es.unican.ctr.marte2mast.files
Class Mast

java.lang.Object
  es.unican.ctr.marte2mast.files.Mast

public class Mast
extends java.lang.Object

This class contains a series of methods used to invoke the MAST tool and recover the data from its output files.

The methods openGmast and recoverMastResults are called from the marte2mast.mtl template (Acceleo). Both methods only do something if the relevant properties of the SaAnalysisContext in the input model say so.

openGmast

public static void openGmast(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Element theElement,
                             java.lang.String thePath)
                      throws java.io.IOException,
                             java.lang.InterruptedException
Invokes MAST graphical tool (GMAST). MAST needs to be installed in a folder called 'mast' inside the root of the Eclipse installation, i.e. "/eclipse/mast"

Parameters:
theElement - UML element from which it's called in Acceleo
thePath - not used, the method's code should be updated to eliminate it
Throws:
java.io.IOException
java.lang.InterruptedException

recoverMastResults

public static void recoverMastResults(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Model theModel)
Parses the .xml output file from MAST, a GUI asks for its path, modifies the UML model with the necessary changes and saves it to a file in the target folder (the same folder where Acceleo saves the rest of the files generated, i.e. the .mast model, the log file...).

This method calls extractDataFromXML and saveModel2File.

Parameters:
theModel - The UML Model

extractDataFromXML

public static boolean extractDataFromXML()
Parses the .xml output file from MAST, a GUI asks for its path, and updates the relevant data in the UML model.

true if everything went right, false if not
